  "referenceWavelength": 550,
  "notes": "k-sign validation with a BURIED absorber (metal-dielectric / induced-transmission style stack). SiO2(50) / Ag(20) / SiO2(50) on BK7. Ag = Johnson & Christy 1972; SiO2 = Malitson 1965 (n=1.4599 @550nm); BK7 = Schott. Symmetric SiO2 spacing so layer order is unambiguous. REFERENCE (independent TMM, N=n+ik): Ellipsometry AOI=65 deg, 550 nm -> Psi=42.68 deg, Delta=264.62 deg (Woollam/Fujiwara). R/T/A at normal incidence, 550 nm -> R=0.5271, T=0.4344, A=0.0386 (R+T+A=1). FIXED build reproduces Delta=264.62 deg; OLD build gives Delta=95.45 deg. Best window to see the difference here: E-field profile through the buried Ag and the Admittance locus. See tools/VALIDATION_README.md."
}
